Fac, precor, optime Erasme, ne posthac tot menses nos crucies expectatione tuarum litterarum, quot proxime cruciasti. Inter- ea hi Erasmomastiges somniant quod optant, et eiusmodi somnia audent etiam spargere in vulgus perinde atque res veras. Illis semper 30 somnia falsa, tibi perpetuum vita incolumis, alacris et leta!

Mechlinie 18a Martii.

Humanitatis tuae discipulus obseruantissimus, Hermanus Lethmatius Goudanus.

1351. FROM PETER WYOHMAN.

Leipzig Ms. Malines. EE. 13. 22 March 152&

[An original letter, autograph throughout. Erasmus’ letter, which it answers, is not extant. It is surprising that he should have so far doubted the loyalty of his old friend and host (see Ep. 1231) as to write and charge him with hostile criticism. The interpretation of the year-date is given in the text3 and this is confirmed by the reference to Ep. 1324]
